<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-23T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/1077: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-23T15:00:00-04:00">May 23, 1936—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>125. Your 254, May 23, 1 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Has there been press comment in regard to the measures of monetary
                                reform and the statements of May 18 made by Kung and the United
                                States Treasury Department? If so, please summarize.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Please amplify statements that “Kung’s statement is confusing and
                                unnecessarily disturbing” and that “the psychological effect has
                                been bad”.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Reports from Hankow and Shanghai indicate that the measures of
                                monetary reform were well received there.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>Report promptly by radio.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>